AICP Protocol Productization — Full Artifacts Checklist (Documents + Folders)
Version: draft checklist v1
Purpose: one-stop checklist to verify the protocol is fully “productized” (implementable, testable, adoptable).

================================================================================
0) Repository / Archive Top Level
================================================================================
/ (root)
  README.md
    - Quickstart (validator-only, agent implementation, external enforcer)
    - Compatibility marks (AICP-Core-0.1, +EXT-..., supported bindings)
    - How to run schemas validation + conformance runner + golden transcripts
    - How to report issues / submit extensions

  CHANGELOG.md
    - Release notes and compatibility guidance

  RELEASE_NOTES.md
    - Current release summary (RC/GA), known issues, migration notes

  VERSION
    - Single source of truth for release version (e.g., 0.1.0-rc.1)

  LICENSE
    - Code license (e.g., Apache-2.0 / MIT)

  SPEC-LICENSE
    - Specification text license (e.g., CC-BY-4.0) if separate from code

  PATENT-POLICY.md
    - Patent/non-assert policy (if applicable)

  CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
    - Community participation rules

  CONTRIBUTING.md
    - How to contribute specs, tests, registries, implementations

  SECURITY.md
    - Vulnerability disclosure policy and security contact

  GOVERNANCE.md
    - Stewardship model, decision-making, roles, release process

  .gitignore
  .editorconfig
  .gitattributes

  /assets
    - Logos, badges, diagrams used in docs

================================================================================
1) Specifications (Docs)
================================================================================
/docs
  /suite
    AICP_Suite_Overview.md (or .docx/.pdf)
      - Umbrella overview: positioning, layers, Core + Registered Extensions catalog
      - Pointers to normative Core + individual extension RFCs

  /core
    AICP_Core_v0.1_Normative.md (and/or .docx/.pdf)
      - Normative language (MUST/SHOULD), Core message types, state machine
      - Crypto/canonicalization profiles (Core)
      - Conformance requirements (Core)

    AICP_Core_v0.1_Schemas_Reference.md
      - Human-readable commentary mapping Core concepts to JSON Schemas

  /rfc
    RFC_Registries_and_Change_Control.md
    RFC_Error_Model_and_Recovery.md
    RFC_Interop_Plugfest_and_Security_Review.md
    RFC_Governance_and_IPR.md (if not in root GOVERNANCE/PATENT-POLICY)

  /extensions
    RFC_EXT_CAPNEG.md               (Capability & Profile Negotiation)
    RFC_EXT_OBJECT_RESYNC.md        (Object/State resync & retrieval)
    RFC_EXT_POLICY_EVAL.md          (Policy evaluation semantics/bindings)
    RFC_EXT_IDENTITY_LIFECYCLE.md   (Key rotation, revocation, migration, attestations)
    RFC_EXT_WORKFLOW_SYNC.md        (Workflow sync primitives, enforceable hooks)
    RFC_EXT_DELEGATION.md           (Hierarchical, purpose-oriented delegation)
    RFC_EXT_DISPUTES.md             (Challenge/claim/arbitration)
    RFC_EXT_SECURITY_ALERTS.md      (Security alerts, evidence bundles)

  /bindings
    RFC_BIND_MCP.md                 (AICP over MCP binding)
    RFC_BIND_HTTP_WS.md             (AICP over HTTP/WebSocket binding)
    RFC_BIND_MESSAGE_BUS.md         (AICP over message bus binding)

  /guides
    Implementers_Guide.md
      - Common pitfalls, recipes, examples, migration guidance
    Enforcer_Guide.md
      - How third-party enforcement works; verification checklist
    Threat_Model.md
      - Threats, mitigations, assumptions, out-of-scope
    Glossary.md
      - Central glossary aligned with Core

